---
description: Node.js and TypeScript backend engineering rules for maintainable APIs, workers, and BFF services.
globs:
  - "**/*.ts"
  - "**/*.js"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use this rule when working on Node.js or TypeScript backend code.
- First clarify the framework, runtime shape, and package manager.
- Keep `controller`, `service`, `repository`, and `jobs` responsibilities separate.
- Do not place complete business workflows in route handlers.
- Handle timeout, retry, idempotency, and shutdown behavior explicitly.
